    "summary": "I am an Assistant Professor and researcher at the Radboud University in The Netherlands. My teaching & research interests are interdisciplinary in Language, Culture, and Communication studies. \n\nI work on concepts in Intercultural communication, Language & Culture, Sociocultural inclusion & equality, African sociolinguistics and Youth language, and International business communication. My research is based on two main areas i.e. in African sociolinguistics and in Diversity & Inclusion. \n\nIn African sociolinguistics, I mainly investigate African youth languages & culture, including the youth\u2019s societal practices portrayed in social media, creative arts and entertainment in narratives, music, movies etc.\n\nIn the field of Diversity and Inclusion, my research and funding contributes to my expertise as a trainer in creating competence and encouraging the application of equal inclusion of all cultures in the global context, especially in international academic institutions. My vision is to ensure a culturally safe and inclusive environment globally.\nIn line with this, I am the chairperson of the Special Interest Group (SIG) Africa, in the Society for Intercultural Education, Training and Research (SIETAR) association.",
